article.headline: Prairie View A&M 66, Texas Southern 65
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Brian Ezeh hit a layup as time expired, and Prairie View A&M rallied from a 19-point deficit to beat Texas Southern 66-65 Saturday night. Derek Johnson hit a free throw to bring Prairie View A&M (5-17, 3-7 SWAC) within 65-64 with three seconds left. Johnson missed his second foul shot, but Ezeh grabbed the offensive rebound and put in the winning basket at the buzzer to give the Panthers their third straight win. Texas Southern (10-11, 6-4) took a 56-37 lead with 11:01 left on Dominique White's 3-pointer. But the Tigers did not have a field goal the rest of the way as they missed their final six shots and turned the ball over eight times. Texas Southern still led 63-52 with 3:34 left, but Prairie View scored the next 10 points and got within 63-62 on Dominique Sharpe's jumper in the lane with 34 seconds remaining. White hit a free throw to put Texas Southern ahead 65-63 with 11 seconds left before Prairie View A&M won the game at the end. Prairie View A&M's Andy Genao had 16 points, and Ezeh scored 15 points and grabbed six rebounds. Jacque Jones scored 21 points for Texas Southern, and Chris Moore had 10 points and 13 rebounds.
